unless you offered 51% don't go.

00:26:41.470 --> 00:26:43.880
And instead he says, why
don't you go to Washington.

00:26:43.880 --> 00:26:47.390 position:56%
She comes to Washington, you can see
her there interviewing Roy Wilkins.

00:26:47.390 --> 00:26:50.100
The man to the right
with the cigar is,

00:26:50.100 --> 00:26:54.290
my mind's gone it'll take a second.

00:26:54.290 --> 00:26:56.850
Gosh, this is really embarrassing.

00:26:56.850 --> 00:26:59.430
He's the first African-American
correspondent

00:26:59.430 --> 00:27:02.070
in the White House
press corps and in

00:27:02.070 --> 00:27:05.950 position:56%
about three seconds he'll come back,
so please excuse my senior moment.

00:27:05.950 --> 00:27:10.400
He's Republican and he's quite
nervous about what Ethel Payne

00:27:10.400 --> 00:27:12.400
and Alice Dunnigan,
the two black women

00:27:12.400 --> 00:27:13.700
in the press corps are going to do.

00:27:13.700 --> 00:27:15.570
And I'll tell you a little
more about that later.

00:27:15.570 --> 00:27:18.090
So anyways, so let's
get back to that moment.

00:27:18.090 --> 00:27:22.560
Here we are in February of 1954,
Ethel Payne is really furious

00:27:22.560 --> 00:27:26.990
so she says to the president,
Mr. President, what's happened

00:27:26.990 --> 00:27:31.640
with this business of the Howard
